abstract: >-
  Prompt as a Process (PaaP) is a framework for treating Markdown SOPs as
  deployable applications, runnable end-to-end by sufficiently reliable
  language models. This repository formalizes the framework via 22
  architectural principles with archetype-aware applicability, a
  scoring rubric, an evaluation instrument (`/paap-eval`), an N=80
  community-skill empirical survey across 36 distinct authors, a
  3-persona inter-rater kappa pilot (mean inter-rater 1.83 grade-steps),
  a head-to-head experiment comparing hand-written vs generated skills
  (blind judge could not distinguish provenance for a humanizer task),
  and a runnable example. Intended for practitioners authoring or
  evaluating LLM workflow files (e.g., SKILL.md), and researchers
  studying the post-orchestration-framework ecosystem.
